The comprador bourgeoisie are non-capitalist [[bourgeoisie]] who owe their existence to imperialist capitalists but cannot function on their own as a capitalist class. In Marxist terms, comprador bourgeoisie exist in developing countries and act in their own economic interests, often sacrificing national interests and the interests of their country's [[proletariat]] in order to do so. The concept of "comprador bourgeoisie" generally ties in with [[Marxism]] and [[dependency theory]].

